<h2>Conclusive land titling&nbsp;</h2>
<p>Presumptive land titling - based on details of past transactions.<br />
Conclusive land titling&nbsp;<br />
title granted by govt which takes responsibility for accuracy. So, claimant has to settle claim with government.</p>
<table border="1" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="1" style="width:500px">
<tbody>
<tr>
	<td>
	<h3>Why?&nbsp;</h3>
	<p><br />
	MONEY = gone (litigation reduced) + came (property tax + agri credit)<br />
	MARKET = EoDB (investment + clear policy) + inefficiency gone (Black market gone)</p></td>
	<td>1. litigations reduced. WB study Land disputes = 2/3 of all court cases , NITI aayog - avg. resolution in land titling case is 20y.<br />
	2. Investment promote<br />
	3. Hurdles to housing project removed. Active land market in country.&nbsp;<br />
	4. Property tax - data based.&nbsp;<br />
	5. No black market which thrives on transaction based titling.<br />
	6. Rural - agri credit = access to formal credit.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>provisions bill</td>
	<td>1. Land authorities by State govt.&nbsp;<br />
	2. TRO - TItle registration officer&nbsp;<br />
	3. LDRO - land dispute resolution officer - &nbsp;Publish record of titles by LDRO</td>
</tr>
<tr>
	<td>Challenges&nbsp;</td>
	<td><br />
	1. rural and semi-urban : land records not updated since decades<br />
	2. Local govt not given enough authority for land titling.</td>
